sentences: Tina Korhonen is a Finnish born music photographer based in the United Kingdom .
She is well known for her portraits of musicians, usually in the rock, punk and heavy rock genres including Europe, Ronnie James Dio
Some of her work, like a striking portrait of Lemmy is on view in the Pipeline Bar in Hoxton.
A photo by Tina of Grammy award winner Bobby Mcferrin appeared in The Guardian newspaper on 31 May 2010.
Tina was one of seven photographers recently featured in a Nikon Pro feature on their website.
